<section class="faq-section">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">Do I need to register a business to sell online in Ukraine?</div>
<div class="faq-a">Yes. To sell legally in Ukraine, you need to register as a FOP (sole proprietor) or create an LLC. Most small online stores start as FOP Group 3, which allows annual revenue up to approximately 8.3 million UAH with a 5% tax rate. Registration can be done online through the Diia portal in 1-2 business days.</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">Which platform is best for a Ukrainian online store?</div>
<div class="faq-a">For beginners, Prom.ua or Horoshop offer the fastest launch with built-in Ukrainian marketplace traffic. For more control and branding, Shopify or WooCommerce are popular choices. Many successful Ukrainian sellers start on Prom.ua to validate demand, then build a standalone website as they grow. Your fulfillment partner like MTP Group integrates with all of these platforms.</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">How long does it take to launch an online store in Ukraine?</div>
<div class="faq-a">A basic store on Prom.ua or Shopify can be set up in 3-5 days. Adding professional photography, custom branding, and a full product catalog typically takes 2-4 weeks. Business registration takes 1-2 days. Onboarding with a fulfillment partner like MTP Group takes 3-5 days. From concept to first sale, most stores launch within 3-6 weeks.</div>
</div>
